name: stillwater-national-wildlife-refuge-and-stillwater-wildlife-management-area-annual-water-m-58393
notes: An estimated 70,000 acre feet(AF) of water are needed annually to maintain 14,000 acres of marsh currently administered by the Stillwater NWR. The 1993 water projections forecast a 100% irrigation delivery year starting on March 22 ending in mid-November. This equates to approximately 21,000- 31,500 AF of return flows to maintain 6,300-14,000 acres at SNWR based on projected water storage and releases at Lahontan Reservoir. Due to prolonged drought conditions, return flows are expected to be significantly delayed once irrigation season commences in late March. Stillwater NWR presently, has available 3,510 AF of acquired water.
